author: National Geographic
description:
Grand Teton
A cast of animals, from tiny pikas to world-famous grizzly bears, tough it out to survive in this iconic, wild wonder of the West

Biscayne
Just below Miami, hidden beneath the waves, is a giant nursery - Biscayne National Park - where thousands of animals come to rear their young.

Channel Islands
Discovering Channel Islands-a hidden chain of wild islands lying in plain sight of Los Angeles, home to plants and animals found nowhere else.

Lake Clark
Lake Clark National Park is a hidden gem where animals, plants and people all coexist in harmony as they have for thousands of years.

Voyageurs
A hidden gem, tucked away in a corner of Minnesota.  Experience its wildlife and stunning beauty from the icy grips of winter to summer blooms. 

America's National Parks | S2, E1-5
